text:
"Nyctimystes bivocalis" is a frog from Papua New Guinea. It lives in the Cloudy Mountains and part of the Owen Stanley Mountains in Milne Bay Province.
The adult male frog is 3.9 to 4.9 cm long and gray-brown in color and the adult female is 4.2 to 5.6 cm long and orange-brown in color.
The name "bivocalis" or "double-voice" comes from the frog's voice. It calls out with two tones.
